lington-1-8-to-4-9v-because-rds-on-resistance-beats-saturation-voltage","line":44},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":47},{"title":"power-systems","target":"power-systems","line":48},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":49}],"metadata":{"description":"The TB6612's 13.5V motor supply ceiling locks out 24V and 36V motors, forcing selection of the less-efficient L298N (46V max) despite the Darlington's heat and loss penalty — efficiency and voltage range are independent axes, and the motor's own voltage rating decides which axis dominates","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/osepp-tb6612-motor-shield-drives-2-dc-motors-at-1p2a-per-channel.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[actuators]]","[[power-systems]]","[[shields]]"],"related_components":["osepp-tb6612-motor-shield","l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/tb6612-motor-supply-ceiling-of-13-5v-is-a-hard-selection-boundary-against-l298n-for-24v-and-36v-motor-systems.md"},"smart_blocks:knowledge/tb6612-motor-supply-ceiling-of-13-5v-is-a-hard-selection-boundary-against-l298n-for-24v-and-36v-motor-systems.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"ig4k9q","at":1776207993829},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.08730056,0.04735141,-0.00048542,-0.05943274,0.01069435,0.04480777,-0.00234917,0.0684061,0.02436681,0.02085335,0.01820279,-0.03799886,-0.02464947,0.00068625,0.00803575,0.01510041,-0.01046221,-0.02411342,0.02207884,0.0708792,0.06833805,-0.03428969,0.01709598,-0.00806357,0.10039904,-0.0038482,0.0215852,-0.01456404,-0.0087994,-0.24295749,-0.03600251,-0.02794496,0.01197143,-0.01127775,-0.05099133,-0.06294803,-0.04501538,-0.0544637,0.02101031,-0.03827914,0.01164718,-0.02478188,0.0108257,-0.0768331,-0.01852045,0.00396052,0.01798308,-0.02316983,0.02861995,-0.05470265,-0.03620593,0.0038516,0.0246147,-0.0233548,0.01566826,0.01898765,0.06433608,0.05207725,-0.00973988,0.02796219,0.06460295,0.02189461,-0.20887333,